<ol>
  <li><A HREF=#1.0>BibleTime 1.0</A></li>
  <li><A HREF=#0.3>BibleTime 0.3x</A></li>
  <li><A HREF=#0.2>BibleTime 0.2x</A></li>
</ol>

<h3><A NAME="1.0">BibleTime 1.0</A>
<table border>
<tr><td>Mainwindow</td>
<td>
  <ul><li>menubar</li>
    <li>configurable toolbar</li>
    <li>splitted into two parts: the main index and the MDI area for the display windows</li>
  </ul>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Main index</td>
<td>
<ul><li>open display windows</li>
  <li>open the search dialog to search in one or more modules</li>
  <li>create, delete, import, export, print, drag and drop bookmarks</li>
  <li>create and delete groups.</li>
  <li>Supports drag & drop</li>
  <li>Saves and restores the positions of bookmarks, groups and modules.</li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>MDI area</td>
<td><ul><li>Manages the display windows</li>
  <li>Tile and cascade the windows</li>
  <li>Supports automatically tiling and cascading of the windows
    if the MDI area was resized or a new window was opened or closed</li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Display windows</td>
<td><ul><li>For every type of module there's one type of displaer with a special interface
  (Bibles, Commentaries, Lexicons)</li>
	<li>Edit mode in Commentary displayers with WYSIWYG html editing</li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Search interface</td>
<td><ul><li>Search text in modules</li>
  <li>You can search more than one module</li>
  <li>Supports three different search methods (Exact phrase,
    Multiple words, Regular expressions)</li>
  <li>Graphical search analysis</li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Printing interface</td>
<td><ul><li>You can print keys (e.g. bookmarks, search results, verses) with a range</li>
  <li>The items which should be printed are collected in the printerqueue</li>
  <li>You can assign styles(formatting rules) to the print items
  <li>You can create, edit, import (later), export (later) and delete styles.</li>
  <li>"Preview" function</li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Help systemy</td>
<td><ul><li>"What's this?" and Tooltip help on most of the UI.</li>
  <li>Handbook</li>
  <li>Helpdialogs</li>
</ul>
</td></tr></table>

<H3><A name="0.3">BibleTime 0.3x</A></H3>
<table border>
<tr><td>Easy to use interface</td>
<td><UL><LI>Divided in two parts: The groupmanager and the MDI area</LI>
  <LI>Space saving arrangement</LI>
  <LI>Automatic switching of fonts if a bible was selected which
    uses a special font</LI>
  <LI>Drag and Drop everywhere</LI>
    <UL>
      <LI>Drag verse references</LI>
      <LI>Drag search results in the groupmanager</LI>
      <LI>Drag verse references in the notes editor - the text of the verse will be pasted</LI>
    </UL>
  <LI>Verse references may be used as hyperlinks</LI>
</UL></td></tr>
<tr><td>Powerful search-interface</td>
<td><UL><LI>Searching for multi words</LI>
  <LI>Searching for exact phrase</LI>
  <LI>Searching with standard GNU regular expressions</LI>
  <LI>Search case (in)sensitive</LI>
  <LI>Define a search scope: last search, own bounds</LI>
  <LI>Improved graphical search analysis</LI>
  <UL>
    <LI>Analyse results of more than one searched module</LI>
    <LI>Save the search analysis as an image</LI>
    <LI>Better represatation of results</LI>
    </UL>
</UL></td></TR>
<tr><td>Easy to use commentary interface</td>
<td><UL><LI>A special presenter for commentaries</LI>
  <LI>Add comments to every writable commentary module</LI>
  <LI>Edit every writable commentary module</LI>
  <LI>Delete your own personal comments</LI>
</UL></td></tr>
<tr><td>Bookmark interface</td>
<td><UL><LI>The bookmark interface is integrated in the groupmanager</LI>
  <LI>Bookmarks may ba arranged in different groups</LI>
  <LI>Possible actions:</LI>
  <UL>
    <LI>add bookmarks either using Drag&Drop or the RMB menu</LI>
    <LI>delete bookmarks</LI>
    <LI>move bookmarks per Drag&Drop</LI>
    <LI>Export bookmarks to a file to share them with others</LI>
    <LI>Import bookmarks from a file to use bookmarks from other users</LI>
  </UL>
</UL></td></tr>
</table>

<H3><A name="0.2">BibleTime 0.2x</A></H3>
<table BORDER>
<tr><td>Easy to use interface</td>
<td><UL><LI>Divided in sizeable parts</LI>
  <LI>Space saving arrangement</LI>
  <LI>Accelerators for the important actions</LI>
  <LI>Automatic switching of fonts if a bible was selected which
  uses a special font</LI>
</UL></td></tr>
<tr><td>Powerful search-interface</td>
<td><UL><LI>Searching for multi words</LI>
  <LI>Searching for exact phrase</LI>
  <LI>Searching with standard GNU regular expressions</LI>
  <LI>Possibility to search case sensitive</LI>
  <LI>searchscope: last search, bounds</LI>
</UL></td></tr>
<tr><td>Easy to use commentary interface</td>
<td><UL><LI>Extra commentary browserwidget</LI>
  <LI>Adding of comments to the personal comments</LI>
  <LI>Possiblity to edit the personal comments</LI>
  <LI>Possibility to delete your own personal comments</LI>
  <LI>Spellchecking of your comments</LI>
</UL></td></tr>
<tr><td>Bookmark interface</td>
<td><UL><LI>Arrangement in different groups</LI>
  <LI>You can add, delete and move bookmarks</LI>
</UL></td></tr>
<tr><td>Printing support</td>
<td><UL><LI>You can add different parts to one print job</LI>
  <LI>Printing with colors for the text and the keys</LI>
  <LI>Printing of headline and footer</LI>
</UL></td></tr>
<tr><td>Optionsdialog</td>
<td><UL><LI>Configuration of general features like "Tip of the day"</LI>
  <LI>Configuration of the different key accelerators</LI>
  <LI>Configuration of the aliases to fonts used by some bibles</LI>
  <LI>Options for printing (e.g. text color, headline printing)</LI>
  <LI>Configuration of browser fonts and colors</LI>
  <LI>Options for the comment spellchecker</LI>
</UL></td></tr>
</table>
